comments: Dinwiddie (DAL) and Poeltl (SAS) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) establishes himself in Sochan's (SAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.

Powell (DAL) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Johnson's (SAS) path and absorbs the contact as Johnson lowers his shoulder and drives through Powell's space on the pick. The play was reviewed to see if it met the criteria of a flagrant foul, and after discussing it with the Replay Center, it did not and remained a common foul.
Poeltl (SAS) extends his hand outward and initiates contact to Powell's (DAL) face as he gathers the entry pass.
Jones (SAS) establishes himself in Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Doncic (DAL) moves alongside Sochan's (SAS) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Powell (DAL) initiates contact with Poeltl's (SAS) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Johnson (SAS) grasps and then quickly releases Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) jersey off-ball and prior to the inbound pass.
Dinwiddie (DAL) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with Sochan (SAS) during the screen, causing him to naturally backpedal. Both players engage and separate from the incidental contact.
Wood (DAL) is imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Doncic (DAL) retracts his resting off-hand from Johnson's (SAS) side, and marginal contact occurs as he releases away at the end of the drive.
Johnson (SAS) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Doncic's (DAL) arm after the release.
Ntilikina (DAL) places his arm to Jones' (SAS) front as he defends over the pick and marginal arm contact occurs.
Poeltl (SAS) establishes himself in Ntilikina's (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Jones (SAS) goes to, not through, Ntilikina (DAL) and marginal body contact occurs as they come together at the same spot during the drive.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) establishes himself in Sochan's (SAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Dinwiddie (DAL) briefly grasps Johnson's (SAS) jersey and immediately disengages during his drive.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) and Johnson (SAS) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) immediately slides his hand off of Poeltl's (SAS) side and marginal contact occurs during the screen.
Dinwiddie (DAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Johnson (SAS) goes to, not through, Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) space and marginal contact occurs as Johnson (SAS) releases away during the drive.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) brings his arm toward Johnson's (SAS) path and marginal contact occurs during Johnson's (SAS) drive.
Wood (DAL) jumps vertically and is collapsing his left forearm when incidental body contact occurs during Sochan's (SAS) driving shot attempt.
Sochan (SAS) dislodges the ball as he brings his arm toward Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) path in the backcourt.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) loses control of the ball after Sochan (SAS) dislodges it and legally regains possession to continue his dribble.
Jones (SAS) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Hardaway Jr. (DAL) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Doncic (DAL) retreats and jumps alongside Sochan's (SAS) path when marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Johnson (SAS) makes marginal contact to Ntliikina (DAL) as he gathers the loose ball.
Sochan (SAS) commits a take foul on Doncic (DAL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Sochan (SAS) takes longer than 5 seconds to release the inbounds pass.
Dinwiddie (DAL) briefly grasps Jones' (SAS) arm before correcting.
Dinwiddie (DAL) engages and disengages with Collins (SAS) and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Collins (SAS) establishes himself in Dinwiddie's (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Ntilikina (DAL) commits a take foul on Jones (SAS). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Poeltl (SAS) and Wood (DAL) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Bertans (DAL) dislodges Jones (SAS) from his rebounding position, which affects his ability to pursue the loose ball.
Soschan (SAS) commits a take foul on Doncic (DAL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
